pageContext.claim: “Biden has even pledged to terminate our travel ban jihadist regions, jihadist regions. They've already been doing that.”
pageContext.analysis: Biden has pledged to end Trump's travel ban, which initially blocked travelers from majority-Muslim countries. The ban now covers Iran, Libya, North Korea, Somalia, Syria and Yemen, as well as immigrants from Eritrea, Kyrgyzstan, Myanmar and Nigeria, and select people from Tanzania and Venezuela. It's not accurate to call these "jihadist regions."
